      "note_no": "100",
      "note": "Most of the commentators - including Tabari, Zamakhshari and Razi - explain the expression la tuharrimu (lit., \"do not forbid\" or \"do not declare as forbidden\") in the sense given by me above, and take it to refer to the self-mortification practiced, in particular, by Christian priests and monks. The term at-tayyibat comprises all that is good and wholesome in life - \"the delightful things which human beings desire and towards which their hearts incline\" (Tabari): hence my rendering, \"the good things of life\"."
